Saladine and his friends, being conquerd with ſuch potent perſwaſions, and already diſmounted from their horſes, ſaw that all deniall was meerly in vaine: and therefore thankfully condiſcen •
ing (after ſome few ceremonious complements were ouer-paſt) the Gentlemen conducted them to their Chambers, which were moſt ſumptuouſly prepared for them, and hauing laid aſide their riding garments, being a little refreſhed with Cakes and choice Wines;
they deſcended into the dining Hall, the pompe whereof I am not able to report.
